ce:section.ce:para:
Nitrogen adsorption-desorption experiments were performed to investigate the specific surface area of Co (0), Co@caffeine, Co@CQD, Co@CQD-MOF(water) and Co@CQD-MOF(ethanol) samples (Fig. 6
                         and Table 1
                        ). Isotherms obtained for all samples indicate type IV isotherm mesoporous formation. The specific surface areas of Co (0), Co@caffeine, Co@CQD, Co@CQD-MOF(water) and Co@CQD-MOF(ethanol) samples were found as 14.36, 32.41, 17.72, 43.80 and 25.30 m2/g, respectively. There is an increase in the surface area of the samples with the support materials compared to the Co (0) catalyst. The porous nature of these nanocomposites has been established by BJH pore size studies. The average pore sizes of the same samples are 27.33, 14.25, 12.78, 10.75 and 14.97 nm, respectively. The average pore sizes obtained by the BJH method are compatible with the pore sizes obtained by TEM analysis.
